Time Complexity:

Let d = number of digits in n

    Reversing digits → O(d)

Overall: O(d)


Space Complexity:

    No extra space used (only variables)

Overall: O(1)


Approach:

1. Store original number in variable n

2. Initialize:
   - x = n (for processing)
   - rev = 0 (to store reversed number)

3. Reverse the number:
   - While x != 0:
     → Extract last digit (x % 10)
     → Append to rev → rev = rev * 10 + digit
     → Remove last digit (x = x / 10)

4. Compute absolute difference:
   - result = |n - rev|

5. Return result





class Solution {
    public int mirrorDistance(int n) {
        int x = n;
        int rev = 0;
        while(x!=0){
            rev = rev*10 + x%10;
            x/=10;
        }
        return Math.abs(n - rev);
    }
}
